		<td><b>Re: new to NES, layering simulation effect question</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />YY-CHR lets you horizontally move blocks of graphics very easily.<br />Where it says &quot;x8&quot; is the zoom setting.  Reduce this, and it fits more tiles into the editing area.<br />Get the editing area to be 32x32 pixels, then hit the &quot;Shift to Right&quot; button.  Instant shifted graphics.  Just need to copy paste a bunch of times, and hit it again.<br /><br />It's a two minute job to copy-paste-shift in YY-CHR.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


