	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Bucky O'Hare has probably the most extensive use of parallax/split effects. It does CHR cycling parallax backgrounds for many levels. Lots of levels have 3 or 4 splits onscreen for multiple large moving objects. I can't think of any other NES game that goes quite so far with it. I don't think it ever does CHR and split effects at the same time, though.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


